 that a saturated MB law, which\nwas previously found to describe the spin-down of rapidly rotating isolated M\ndwarfs, also operates in tidally locked binaries. We advocate using saturated\nMB models in binary evolution calculations. Our work supports previous\nsuggestions that MB in cataclysmic variables (CVs) is much weaker than assumed\nin the standard evolutionary model, unless mass transfer leads to significant\nadditional angular momentum loss in CVs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Aug 2022 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 11 Oct 2022 14:47:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-26"}
